    {
      "name": "Mass spectrometry",
      "protocol_type": {
        "source": "CHMO",
        "accession": "CHMO:0000470",
        "name": "mass spectrometry"
      },
      "description": "The derivatized sample was injected (3 µl) split ratio of 10 into a Thermo Electron Trace GC Ultra equipped with amino acid column (Phenomenex; injector temperature = 220 °C, helium carrier gas flow rate = 1.1 ml/min). The initial column temperature was 110 °C; this was held for 2 min and then increased by 30 °C/min to 310 °C. The column effluent was introduced into a Trace DSQ quadrupole mass spectrometer (Thermo Electron; transfer line temperature = 320 °C, ion source temperature = 240 °C, electron beam = 70 eV). The detector was turned on after a solvent delay of 120 s, and data were collected in full scan mode using 3 scans/s across a mass range of 50–450 m/z.",
