    {
      "name": "Data transformation",
      "protocol_type": {
        "source": "OBI",
        "accession": "OBI:0200000",
        "name": "data transformation"
      },
      "description": "GC-MS chromatograms were analyzed using Xcalibur, version 2.0 (Thermo Electron), integrating each peak individually. Each integrated peak was normalized so that the total sum of peaks was set to 10,000. Deconvolution of overlapping peaks was achieved by traces of single ions. A 0.1 min threshold window was used for the deviation of peaks away from the predicted retention time across the data set."
